    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.10.20-22_0001" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">20</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ALLEN TUPPER TRUE
                        <lb/>
                    DENVER, COLORADO</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        1425 St. Paul St.
                        Oct. 1. 1923
                    </dateline>
                
                    <salute>My Dear Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Delighted to hear that you are going to lecture out West this winter and in Colorado perhaps. I am off for Santa Fe about the 15th and cannot help your Mr. Long arrange the engagement here in Denver altho<sic>although</sic> I have put him in touch with the proper parties. How I wish I could be here to <unclear>shoot</unclear> it up for a man I do so deeply believe in! But after Santa Fe we head for London Eng for a year where the rest of the <unclear>Ms.</unclear> Capital <unclear>pendenterÃªs</unclear> 
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.10.20-22_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                    
                    will be done along with some assisting <unclear>Branquerye</unclear>, my old master, on the work he is doing for Missouri. My "Indian" Memories" go up into place this week and next and I'm busy as a setter <unclear>pup</unclear> &#8212; and about as useful.</p> 
                
                <p>What did you think of my suggeston for making a lot of pen and ink <unclear/> sketches, tail pieces. etc for the Song of the Indian Wars when it is published I wrote you fully about this but never heard from you. Perhaps it is still before the publishers? There will not be much time for large serious illustration but I might do the aforementioned thing and I'd like to be identified with the work if I could be. Some of my paintings might be used 
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.10.20-22_0003"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                
                    and I send under separate cover a photo of one. Cost is no consideration if the stuff will do.</p>
                
                <p>And when will the books be published?</p>
                
                <p>I read that you were to be in Lincoln some time soon. When there mention me as a murral<sic>mural</sic> painter if you see an opportunity because I am nursing hopes for some work in that capital building.</p>
                
                <p>And as they say on they say on the streets "Take care of yourself."</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Best regards,</salute>
                        <salute>The same</salute>
                            <signed>True</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
